<br>
I'd say go for a TS that is going to benefit your race/class the most and if later on VI adds more recipes for your race in another trade there is an AA you can spend points on to take it up later and get it to GM.<br>
<br>
No matter which trade you choose to take up it's going to cost you some major PP to GM (brewing and baking being the cheapest I think). <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=343243"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ulujain.org/albums/album04/abe.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=351766"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ulujain.org/albums/album04/abf.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
